                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/254</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-21T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1916, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. Consul, Pieclras Negras, reports confiscation of American brewery Sabinas
                    and raid by five Mexicans, including two Carranza officers, on American-owned
                    ranch near Guerrero, and that it appears Governor Coahuila has started vigorous
                    campaign against Americans and their property.</p>
                <p>Insist that governor be immediately ordered to desist from anti-American
                    activities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
